Class MessageUtils

java.lang.Object
dev.bjdelacruz.commons.utils.MessageUtils
public final class MessageUtils extends Object
Utility methods for reading and writing a message, which is just an array of bytes.
A message can be used to communicate between a client and server. Using a message is preferable to using a serialized object for communication.

    • isSerializedObject

      public static boolean isSerializedObject(InputStream inputStream)
      Reads in the first two bytes from the given input stream and returns true if they are a serialized object identifier or false if they are not.

      If this method returns true, the caller of this method can choose to read in the object and then ignore it.

      Parameters:
      inputStream - The input stream from which to read in bytes.
      Returns:
      true if the bytes that were read in represent a message identifier, false otherwise.
